      <div class="article-teaser">
        A scheme to improve traffic in Wandsworth High Street and rejuvenate the town centre is being developed. We currently expect to start the work in 2021.<BR>
        
      </div>
    
    
      <p>The <a href="http://www.ram-brewery.co.uk">Ram Brewery redevelopment</a>, alongside Wandsworth Council's plans to regenerate the town centre, will transform the local area for residents and create new opportunities for businesses. </p>
<p>As part of these changes, we have a plan to decrease traffic dominance in Wandsworth High Street and help rejuvenate the area.</p>
<p>Our proposals include:&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
<ul>
    <li>Reducing through traffic in the town centre, leaving it free for buses, cyclists and local access</li>
    <li> Widening footways</li>
    <li>Improving the local environment</li>
</ul>
<p>A public consultation on the changes proposed for Wandsworth town centre ended in January 2016. The consultation report is on the <a href="https://consultations.tfl.gov.uk/roads/wandsworth-town-centre">Wandsworth town centre consultation page</a>.</p>
      
           
      
