<p>The timeline for this scheme includes a compulsory purchase order (CPO) process to get the additional land we need - this can take 18-24 months.</p>
<p>We hope to begin construction in late 2021. In the meantime, we will be surveying around Wandsworth town centre.</p>
<h2>Survey works from October 2018</h2>
<p>From October 2018, we will do CCTV surveys - using cameras in the drainage system - to check the condition of existing drainage around Wandsworth town centre. We will also be making trial holes in footways to check the location of utility services and ground conditions.</p>
<p>Traffic will still flow at all times, but short-term traffic management changes may be needed. Please allow more time for your journeys</p>
<p>Some short-term bus stop suspensions will be needed during the works. Notices will be put on any affected bus stops.</p>
<p>From 22-24 October 2018, loading and parking bay suspensions will be in place around Wandsworth gyratory between 09:30 and 16:30. Our contractors will be working for about one hour in each loading/parking bay before moving on to the next one to carry out trial holes. The temporary suspensions will be removed once work is finished in each loading/parking bay.</p>
<p>Footways and pedestrian crossings will stay open at all times, although footways will be narrower than usual. Access to properties will not be affected.</p>
